## 10. Export Recovered Data and Reinsert into Source UAT DB

If the restore was done to staging, use export/import to place the recovered rows back into source UAT.

### 10.1 Export from staging

```sh
mkdir -p $DATA_BASE/export

db2 "export to $DATA_BASE/export/T_RESTORE_B.ixf of ixf select * from RCVLAB.T_RESTORE_B"
```

**Paste screenshot reference:**  
`[SCREENSHOT-20: Export from staging]`

---

### 10.2 Import into source DB

```sh
db2 connect to $DB_NAME

db2 "import from $DATA_BASE/export/T_RESTORE_B.ixf of ixf replace into RCVLAB.T_RESTORE_B"
```

If the table no longer exists in source because it was dropped, recreate it first using the same DDL as earlier and then import.

Validate:

```sh
db2 "select * from RCVLAB.T_RESTORE_B order by ID"
```

**Paste screenshot reference:**  
`[SCREENSHOT-21: Data restored back to source UAT DB]`

