## 16. Known Technical Notes

1. In DB2 tablespace recovery work, the exact syntax order matters. In particular, `RESTORE` commands should keep `FROM` / `TAKEN AT` before `INTO`.
2. If a tablespace does not yet exist in the staging restore context, `SET TABLESPACE CONTAINERS` may fail until the redirected restore has been initiated correctly.
3. Row-level recovery is typically safest through **restore to staging + export/import**.
4. Direct restore into the source DB may be possible in some cases, but it is operationally more sensitive and should not be the default test method.

